From: art-suite conda packaging
Subject: [PATCH] Add missing #include <cassert> for assert()

22 translation units / headers call assert() but rely on <cassert> being pulled
in transitively. Older libstdc++ did so; conda-forge's newer libstdc++ (with
C++20) does not, so they fail with "'assert' was not declared in this scope".
Add the explicit include after each file's first #include. Re-derived against
art 3.15.00 (the file set differs from the v3_14_04 recipe). See
potential_improvements.md (#5, #9).

